The Violet Compact names the containment-bureaucracy governance layer that normalized sealed transit, registry masking, and testimony control in Midgaard during the Ash-and-Iron Decades.
The Compact's three principles were: registry primacy (all civic claims require registry entry to have legal standing), containment over destruction (suspected threats are held and audited, not eliminated), and civic oversight of thresholds (all access to dangerous spaces and substances requires documented authorization).
Under the Violet Compact, the Sealed Names apparatus was established — a system for removing individuals' names from public rolls while retaining their records in restricted access archives.
The "resettled south" mechanism allowed officials to reclassify condemned debtors and "unregistered persons" as transferred to labor service, with the transfer destination frequently the Spirebound Conclave in the Cinderteeth Mountains.
The Compact's containment doctrine extended to Sepulchur Pasture, establishing quarantine holding pens for arcane-active remains under the principle that destroyed remains become uncontrollable rumor while contained remains remain auditable.
The Violet Eclipse Cathedral, located along the western approaches from Midgaard, was a threshold institution operating under Compact authorization — reachable but deniable, sanctioned but not fully absorbed into municipal order.
The Violet Reliquary Arch in Midgaard marks the warded descent point into the Gloamvault; the Compact's containment doctrine governed all access to the Arch and the spaces below it.
The Compact is understood by the Reckoning faction as the bureaucratic infrastructure that made the Ash-and-Iron Decades' worst abuses possible while maintaining procedural legibility.
The Continuity faction acknowledges the Compact's excesses but argues that its core principles — registry discipline, containment protocols, authorized access — remain the foundation of functional civic order.
The Compact's registry-masking capability, once established, created permanent institutional temptation to use it beyond its original containment purpose.
The Wizard's Keep was chartered under Violet Compact policy pressure as a supervised academy, and its founding principles reflect Compact doctrine: no unsupervised field trials, every adept tied to a legal witness chain.

