The Violet Compact is the primary political fault line in Midgaard's governance: the Continuity faction defends its principles while the Reckoning faction demands accounting for its methods. The Sealed Names apparatus — names removed from public rolls but retained in restricted archives — is the Reckoning faction's central exhibit of Compact overreach. The 'resettled south' mechanism transferring condemned debtors to the Conclave is connected to the Unindexed Years — missing or duplicated ledgers the Compact's registry-masking capability appears to have enabled. The Violet Reliquary Arch and its connection to the Gloamvault represent the Compact's containment doctrine at its most literal — threshold control over dangerous depths. The Violet Eclipse Cathedral was the Compact's most visible external institution — coercive ritual outside the city's direct oversight circuits. The Compact's registry primacy doctrine remains operative: the Magistrate Ledgerhouse requires registry entry for all legal claims.

