Kowloon's Jade Magistracy operated parallel structures to the Violet Compact's sealed-warrant apparatus during the same period. The Black Ledger — the sealed census of Kowloon individuals transferred to the Conclave — is Kowloon's equivalent of the Sealed Names apparatus. Deltari oral tradition preserves names from the Black Ledger that the official records do not, maintained specifically because the Compact's registry-masking capability was used to erase them. The Ash Cult's theological reading of the Ashfall as punishment for Conclave-era transfers directly implicates the Compact's administrative apparatus. Kowloon's Neon Covenant was partly developed as a counter-institutional framework to the kind of registry capture that the Violet Compact represented.

